Signs.Text: This is a sign. Walk on it to read it.
The thing below is a vortex.
Walk on it to teleport to another location.
It's an @ symbol, either blue or orange.
A blue vortex is an enter vortex.
An orange vortex is an exit vortex.
You can create a vortex by pressing N, then 1.
A vortex can be either one-way, or two-way.
A one-way vortex teleports you to an address.
A two-way vortex teleports you to another vortex.
That vortex, an exit vortex, can take you back.
You can delete a vortex by standing on top of it.
Only entry vortexes (blue) can be deleted.
If you create a one-way vortex, you can delete it:
Create a two-way vortex pointing to its address,..

the helper two-way vortex (the entry vortex).
